<subSubSection id="C301653BFFA9FFFCFF36FA47FCD9F93A" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA436B0FFA9FFFCFF36FA47FED9F9A1" blockId="7.[189,310,1533,1559]" box="[189,310,1533,1559]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading id="D0EC81DCFFA9FFFCFF36FA47FED9F9A1" bold="true" box="[189,310,1533,1559]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B96FEAA2FFA9FFFCFF36FA47FED9F9A1" bold="true" box="[189,310,1533,1559]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA436B0FFA9FFFCFF36F991FCD9F93A" blockId="7.[189,1399,1579,1676]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
The species and genus can be differentiated from all other 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D33FFA9FFFCFC0DF991FC07F9F3" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1905" box="[902,1000,1579,1605]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Stilicina">Stilicina</taxonomicName>
based on the combination of the following characters: the presence of a single median tooth on the labrum, mandibles symmetrical, posterior margin of head rounded, and legs elongated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
